## useNFTList() function

> This API is provided as a preview for developers and may change based on feedback that we receive. Do not use this API in a production environment.
> 

Use this to get a list of NFT tokens of your ERC721 contract.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
declare function useNFTList(contract: RequiredParam<Erc721<any>>, queryParams?: QueryAllParams): react_query.UseQueryResult<_thirdweb_dev_sdk.NFTMetadataOwner[], unknown>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  contract | RequiredParam&lt;Erc721&lt;any&gt;&gt; | an instace of a contract that extends the Erc721 spec (nft collection, nft drop, custom contract that follows the Erc721 spec) |
|  queryParams | QueryAllParams | <i>(Optional)</i> query params to pass to the query for the sake of pagination |

<b>Returns:</b>

react\_query.UseQueryResult&lt;\_thirdweb\_dev\_sdk.NFTMetadataOwner\[\], unknown&gt;

a response object that includes an array of NFTs

## Example


```javascript
const { data: nfts, isLoading, error } = useNFTList(<YourERC721ContractInstance>, { start: 0, count: 100 });
```
